<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-16T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="44" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.96/309a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-16T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6600. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 108. The War Trade Board has established a committee of five to
                                be known as the Contraband Committee, which will, under the
                                supervision of the War Trade Board, handle the administrative
                                problems in connection with the issuance of export licenses in
                                accordance with the general policies of the Board, and also make
                                such rules <pb facs="0129" n="963" xml:id="pg_963"/> and regulations
                                as may be necessary to carry out the instructions of the Board. The
                                actual licensing will continue to be done as heretofore by the
                                Bureau of Exports in accordance with the regulations of the
                                Contraband Committee. Full details follow by mail. Repeat in, full
                                to Christiania, Stockholm, Copenhagen, and The Hague.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>